# Naming conventions

Domain-qualify every generic container name. Bare generics are banned unless there is provably only one in the whole system (registries are not that case).

## Files

- Use `camelCase` with the **domain noun first**: `agentRegistry.ts`, `skillLoader.ts`, `gatewaySession.ts`.
- Never: `registry.ts`, `manager.ts`, `handler.ts`, `service.ts`, `context.ts`, `session.ts`, `store.ts`, `loader.ts`, `util.ts`, `helper.ts` without a domain prefix.

## Types

- Use `PascalCase`, domain-qualified: `AgentRegistration`, `AgentRegistry`, `SkillEntry`.
- Never bare `Registry`, `Entry`, `Record`, `Manager`, `Context` without a domain prefix.

## Registry symmetry

All registries follow `<domain>Registry` + `<Domain>Registration`:

- `agentRegistry` / `AgentRegistration`
- future: `skillRegistry` / `SkillRegistration`, `jobRegistry` / `JobRecord`

## Already compliant examples

- `gatewaySession.ts`, `agentMemory.ts`, `skillLoader.ts`
